Package: edlibR
Title: R Wrapper to Edlib, the C/C++ Library for Fast Exact Sequence Alignment using Edit (Levenshtein) Distance
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(person("Martin", "Šošić", email = "sosic.martin@gmail.com", role = c("aut")), person("Evan", "Biederstedt", email="evan.biederstedt@gmail.com", role=c("aut", "cre")))
Description: The 'edlibr' R provides provides an R API to the C/C++ library edlib, which is a lightweight, super fast library for sequence alignment using edit (Levenshtein) distance. The original algorithm is described in "Edlib: a C/C++ library for fast, exact sequence alignment using edit distance", M. Šošić, M. Šikić, <doi:10.1093/bioinformatics/btw753>.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
Imports: Rcpp (>= 1.0.5), stringr (>= 1.4.0)
Suggests: testthat (>= 3.1.0), rmarkdown, knitr
RoxygenNote: 7.1.2
VignetteBuilder: knitr
URL: https://github.com/evanbiederstedt/edlibR
BugReports: https://github.com/evanbiederstedt/edlibR/issues
NeedsCompilation: yes
LinkingTo: Rcpp
SystemRequirements: C++11
Author: Martin Šošić [aut], Evan Biederstedt [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Evan Biederstedt <evan.biederstedt@gmail.com>
